🧱 B01 — BLOCK 5 of 8 — Create alternate key on pei_rulename
Where: Solutions → Evidence Management System → Tables → Rule → Keys (left-side panel; in some maker-portal versions it's under "Properties → Keys" or in a tab next to Columns).
Click + New key.
Fields:
Display name:
AK Rule Name
Name (auto-derives from display; verify):
pei_AK_Rule_Name
(Some versions show the schema with the pei_ prefix, some without. If yours shows just AK_Rule_Name, that's fine — both work. The display name AK Rule Name is what matters for human recognition.)
Columns (the columns picker — add ONE column):
Rule Name
(The display name. The picker may show schema names in parentheses — confirm pei_rulename is the underlying schema.)
Save.

What happens after Save:
The maker portal kicks off an async index-provisioning job. The Keys list will show the new key with a Status column — initial value is usually In progress or Pending. It refreshes to Active (or Completed) once Dataverse has built the supporting unique index on pei_rulename.
Wait for status = Active before moving on. This usually takes 30 seconds to 2 minutes. Refresh the Keys list to check. If it stalls in Pending for more than 5 minutes, tell me and I'll talk through diagnostics — but it almost always succeeds quickly on a small empty table.

Verbatim checks for the sidecar (once status = Active)
Check B01-15 — Was the alternate key created with display name AK Rule Name on column pei_rulename? (yes / no / partial — describe)
Check B01-16 — Did the key reach status Active / Completed (not stuck Pending)? (yes / no / partial — describe)
Optional reassurance check B01-17 — Try to create a SECOND Rule row with Rule Name = (something already used, e.g., your B01 smoke-test name "Smoke_R1_HostingTypeCloud_Applicable") and confirm the platform rejects it. You haven't created the first smoke-test row yet, so skip this for now — we'll cover it during Block 8 smoke test instead. Don't act on this yet.
(Note: B01-17 is logged in the sidecar but will be answered later, after Block 8 creates the first Rule. We'll come back to it.)
Reply with the two verbatim answers (B01-15 and B01-16) once the key is Active, and I'll give you Block 6 (enable Audit at table level — a fast one).
